<li id="lithub_daily_widget-9" class="widget widget_lithub_daily_widget"><div class="lithub-daily-header"><a href="/category/lit-hub-daily/"><b>Lithub</b> Daily</a></div><h2 class="widgettitle">January 6, 2025</h2>
<a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hub-daily-january-6-2025/"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-247750 size-thumbnail" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/640px-Background_rocks-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a>
<ul>
 	<li><a href="https://theamericanscholar.org/the-weight-of-a-stone/" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">The poetry of geology</span></a></li>
 	<li><a href="https://www.nybooks.com/articles/2025/01/16/far-from-the-seventies-consent-springora-ciment/" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">On two memoirs titled </span><i><span style="font-weight: 400">Consent</span></i></a></li>
 	<li><a href="https://daily.jstor.org/laughing-with-the-fascists/" class="external" target="_blank">The humor of fascists</a></li>
</ul>
<a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hub-daily-january-6-2025/"><button>More News</button></a></li>
